  "prompt": "How much should I aim in my graduation to get into IIM A/B/C assuming I get a 99+ percentile in CAT?",
  "response": "Getting into the Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs), particularly IIM Ahmedabad (A), Bangalore (B), and Calcutta (C), is highly competitive. While a 99+ percentile in the Common Admission Test (CAT) is a strong start, it's just one part of the admission process. Your academic performance during graduation also plays a significant role. Here\u2019s a general guideline on what to aim for in terms of graduation percentage:\n\n### General Guidelines for IIM A/B/C Admissions:\n\n1. **CAT Percentile:** A 99+ percentile in CAT is essential for a strong application to IIM A/B/C. However, the cutoff percentile can vary each year, typically ranging from 99 to 100.\n\n2. **Graduation Percentage:** \n   - **IIM Ahmedabad:** A minimum of 50% in graduation is required, but to be competitive, aim for at least 70-80%.\n   - **IIM Bangalore:** A minimum of 60% in graduation is required, but to be competitive, aim for at least 70-80%.\n   - **IIM Calcutta:** A minimum of 50% in graduation is required, but to be competitive, aim for at least 70-80%.\n\n3. **Class 10th and 12th Marks:** Good scores in these exams (typically above 70-80%) can also strengthen your application.\n\n4. **Work Experience:** While not mandatory, relevant work experience can significantly boost your profile. IIMs often look favorably on candidates with 1-3 years of work experience.\n\n5. **Written Ability Test (WAT) and Personal Interview (PI):** Performance in these components is crucial. A strong academic record can help you perform well in these stages.\n\n### Strategies to Maximize Your Chances:\n\n1. **Focus on Academics:** Aim for the highest possible marks during your graduation. A strong academic record can compensate for any slight dip in CAT percentile.\n\n2. **Extracurricular Activities:** Participate in extracurricular activities, leadership roles, and community service. These can enhance your profile and show your well-rounded personality.\n\n3. **Prepare for WAT and PI:** Work on your communication skills, general awareness, and ability to articulate your thoughts clearly and concisely.\n\n4. **Mock Interviews:** Participate in mock interviews and practice WATs to improve your performance.\n\n5. **Stay Updated:** Keep an eye on the specific admission criteria and weightage given to different components by each IIM, as these can change from year to year.\n\n### Conclusion:\n\nWhile a 99+ percentile in CAT is a strong foundation, aiming for at least a 70-80% graduation percentage is advisable to remain competitive for IIM A/B/C. Additionally, a holistic profile with good academic scores, extracurricular involvement, and strong performance in WAT and PI will significantly enhance your chances of admission.",
